<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="347" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to the British Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Churchill</hi></persName>)<note n="21" type="source" xml:id="d347fn21">Copy of telegram obtained from the
                                Franklin D. Roosevelt Library, Hyde Park, N.Y.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-01">1 October, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>367. Your 427 and 427.<note n="22" xml:id="d347fn22">Dated September 30,
                                    <ref target="#pg_380">p. 380</ref>.</note> Italy has not yet
                            made a declaration of war against Germany.</p>
                        <p>I suggest that you endeavor to obtain from Stalin approval of your text
                            of proposed joint statement by all three of us to be made public
                            immediately following a declaration of war against Germany by Italy.</p>
                        <p>Your text meets with my approval.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>